<table cellspacing="10" style="margin-left:40px; margin-top:5px;">
<tr>
  <td><strong>POSITION:</strong></td><td style="font-size:1.2em; font-weight:bold">Development Coordinator</td></tr>
<tr>
  <td><strong>SUPERVISOR:</strong></td><td>Mary Schrock, Director of Development and Chief Operations Officer</td></tr>
<tr>
  <td><strong>STATUS:</strong></td><td>Full-time,  Exempt</td></tr>
</table>
<p>Position is a member of the &ldquo;PACER  Development Team&rdquo; and participates in all aspects of the department with a concentration  on activities specified below. This position works with volunteers, funders, sponsors,  community representatives, and interfaces with many staff. It is a team-based,  collegial, and energetic environment.</p>
<h2>RESPONSIBILITIES/ROLES</h2>
<ul class="nobullet">
 <li>
   <p><strong>Grant Writing and Promotion</strong></p>
   <ol>
     <li>Conduct grant  research and write grants for PACER&rsquo;s projects</li>
     <li>Call,  communicate, and build relationships with foundation officers</li>
     <li>Make contacts  with new corporations and foundations</li>
     <li>Assist with writing  articles for Development Department&rsquo;s donor newsletter </li>
     <li>Develop content  and provide updates for development web pages</li>
     <li>Coordinate social  media communications for PACER</li>
     <li>Draft letters and other materials for PACER</li>
     <li>Additional duties and responsibilities as needed</li>
     </ol>
 </li>
 <li>
  <p><strong>Annual Benefit and Special Events</strong></p>
   <ol start="1" type="1">
     <li>Provide support for Benefit Performer logistics       prior to Benefit and day of event</li>
     <li>Coordinate development and dissemination (printed       and electronic) of all Annual Benefit promotional materials, including       media materials</li>
     <li>Assist with planning and executing other aspects of       the Benefit, such as raffle, Extravaganza, etc.</li>
     <li>Coordinate promotion, scheduling and logisitics       for large conferences, such as the Symposium</li>
     <li>Assist with development, promotion, and       coordination of special events and projects, including the Benefit</li>
     <li>Provide staff support, as needed, with special       events</li>
     </ol>
 </li>
 <li>
  <p><strong>Committees and Advisory Boards</strong></p>
   <ol>
     <li>Coordinate Young Professionals  Advisory Board including scheduling, agendas, minutes and activities </li>
     <li>Provide staff  support, as needed, with committees</li>
   </ol>
 </li>
</ul>
<h2><strong>REQUIREMENTS and QUALIFICATIONS</strong></h2>
  <ul>
    <li>College degree required</li>
    <li>Excellent verbal  and written communication skills</li>
    <li>Experience in  writing</li>
    <li>Ability to use  discretion and diplomacy when communicating with donors and sponsors</li>
    <li>Excellent  organizational skills, ability to prioritize, and meet deadlines</li>
    <li>Experience in  event planning for conferences with over 1000 participants</li>
    <li>Experience in  coordinating conference agendas, including speaker logistics, participant  logistics and facilities logistics</li>
    <li>Knowledge and sensitivity  to issues, current information, and research related to persons with  disabilities</li>
    <li>Accuracy and  attention to detail</li>
    <li>Ability to manage  multiple tasks on several projects</li>
    <li>Ability to  collaborate with co-workers and coordinate projects</li>
    <li>Ability to work  independently and participate in team planning and decision-making process</li>
    <li>Above average  proficiency of computer software programs; primarily Microsoft Office with an  emphasis on Word, Excel and PowerPoint, and&nbsp;  FileMaker Pro</li>
    <li>Ability to keep  confidentiality about community members, donors, volunteers and staff</li>
    <li>Ability to  develop positive relationships with community members, donors, volunteers, and  staff</li>
  </ul>
<hr />
<p>Salary to be determined based on experience. </p>
<p>Position available  immediately. Parents of children with disabilities are encouraged to apply. </p>
